article.headline: Yale 56, Brown 42
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Sam Kaplan and Casey Hughes led a balanced attack as Yale defeated Brown 56-42 in the Ivy League opener for both teams on Saturday night. Kaplan and Hughes scored 10 points apiece as the Bulldogs (5-9) won for the first time in their past five games at the Pizzitola Sports Center. Mark McAndrew was the only Bear who reached double figures as he scored a game-high 18 points. The 42 points were the fewest Yale has allowed this season while Brown (5-11) has lost four in a row. Brown's Marcus Becker scored the first basket of the game and then Yale went on a 10-0 run during which the Bulldogs held the Bears without a basket for 6:49. Yale increased its lead to 30-15 on three consecutive 3-point baskets -- two by Travis Pinick and a third by Nick Holmes. Brown scored the first six points of the second half and reduced Yale's lead to 30-27. But Yale countered with another 10-0 run that included 3-point baskets by Eric Flato and Caleb Holmes. Damon Huffman's layup stopped that run but 11 points was as close as Brown could get for the rest of the game. Hughes also pulled down a game-high 10 rebounds for a double-double as Yale out-rebounded Brown 34-19. The Bulldogs, who had lost seven of their last eight games to Brown, scored 21 points off 18 Brown turnovers.
